column5: well i hate to say it. but it's that time of year again. to put my boat away for the winter. but we ended with a bang. on our last trip to quinte at Merland park this past week. not less then one fish a day. with Thursday being our best day. with 11 walleye, and 1 sheep head. total for this trip are 20 walleye and one sheep head. lol it was a great year for kim and i with 43 walleye, two northern pike and 18 large mouth bass. seem it's getting better and better each year we come to quinte. well to all enjoy the rest of the season. and we talk next year. happy fishing, see you on the water, walleyedreamer. i add more pictures as i go.
quinte last trip of the year.
more of Kim aka bass dreamer.
